Class AuthError

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class AuthError
extends java.lang.Exception

This class encapsulates errors from External API Methods.

These errors are passed through onError or it can be put into an android.content.Intent android.os.Bundle for an error android.app.Activity result.

Some instances of AuthError will contain a cause which will indicate the Exception that caused this AuthError.

This class also implements android.os.Parcelable so that AuthError objects can be put into a Bundle.

All known errors will create a specific AuthError.ERROR_CATEGORY and AuthError.ERROR_TYPE, along with a message. If there is an exception it will be added to the AuthError cause attribute.

All unhandled exceptions will create an Unknown Error in Unknown Category, along with a message and if there is an exception that triggered this it will be added to the AuthError cause attribute.

See Also:
Parcelable, Bundle, Serialized Form
